1
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:09,080
What?

2
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:12,040
Is someone going to kill me?

3
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:14,240
I just don’t want to lose you again!

4
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:23,720
There’s someone I’d like to introduce to you all.

5
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,240
Hello, everyone.

6
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:32,600
I’m Dean Dithakorn.

7
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:37,560
Dean Dithakorn.
His name wasn’t in any of the data I gathered.

8
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:39,800
But he was at the funeral too.

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:43,440
I want Dean to get close to Lené.

10
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:47,960
You can help me bring them together, can't you?

11
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:00,000
Here’s your coffee.

12
00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:06,720
Why are you smiling so much?

13
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:09,160
Aren’t you tired from smiling all day?

14
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,000
I’m just in a good mood.

15
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:22,800
You have a meeting with
App Development team at 10 a.m.

16
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,560
- And then you—
- Push everything to tomorrow.

17
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Pardon?

18
00:01:31,720 --> 00:01:33,440
I have plans with Khun Dean today.

19
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:45,320
Change today’s schedule to a meeting
with Khun Dean this morning.

20
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:48,039
I’m taking him to the warehouse this afternoon.

21
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:54,000
As for the evening, find us
a nice restaurant for dinner.

22
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:33,920
Get up.

23
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:46,280
I’m only this small.
It’s not like I’m that heavy.

24
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,040
- AAHHH!!!
- Oh! Holy guacamole!

25
00:02:57,200 --> 00:03:00,240
This is literally that love scene
from the show I watched last night.

26
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,280
We'll come back later then.

27
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,160
No need.

28
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:07,880
What is it?

29
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:10,880
But… didn't you ask us
to come in for a meeting?

30
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,760
It's postponed.

31
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:13,720
Huh?

32
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,120
Like I said, it’s postponed.

33
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,000
Understood.

34
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,560
- Don’t you have work to do?
- We're leaving now!

35
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,880
- Everyone, get out!
- The meeting’s postponed.

36
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,160
Wait for me.

37
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,880
Well, well.

38
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,520
Don't forget to lock the door next time.

39
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:57,079
- I knew it!
- I saw the whole thing in 4K, Sis.

40
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:58,680
- I freaking knew it!
- You saw it too, right?

41
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:01,520
Please, you'd have to be blind not to see that.

42
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,480
It’s a shame I didn’t get my phone out in time.

43
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:06,240
- I can’t believe my eyes.
- It was clear as day.

44
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,480
What’s the tea, ladies?

45
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,880
Girl, forget Khun Dean.

46
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,560
He’s nothing compared to
what we just saw in there.

47
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:16,279
I saw it with my own two eyes!
Right, Sis?

48
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:18,279
- Did you see that, Wit?
- Definitely, Sis.

49
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,360
Nong Rann was sitting on Khun Lené’s lap!

50
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,760
Khun Lené, our boss! Khun Ledarin herself!

51
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,720
No way! For real? What happened?!

52
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:30,880
It was just like that scene where
the lead couple shares a kiss in the office

53
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:34,800
I don’t even want to imagine if
we’d walked in just a second later.

54
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:38,960
Even Khun Dean doesn’t stand a chance

55
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:42,800
when Khun Lené has such
a gorgeous secretary at home.

56
00:04:43,159 --> 00:04:45,520
Nong Rann seems quiet,
but she’s actually pretty spicy.

57
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:46,920
Stop! Stop right there!

58
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,600
It wasn’t what you think at all.

59
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,760
- Oh, it was exactly what we think.
- Oh.

60
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:56,760
Or maybe it’s even more than what we’re thinking.

61
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:58,520
For real?

62
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,000
Absolutely.

63
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:03,560
- Ooh! Mr. Know-it-all!
- You have to spill.

64
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,840
- I think I might—
- Quiet!

65
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,640
She’s got ears like a hawk.

66
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:17,520
You should lock the door
when you're up to something.

67
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:20,880
Don’t just be all touchy-feely in there.

68
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,720
Yes, Khun Kanin.

69
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,120
I’ll be there right away.

70
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,680
Please excuse me.

71
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,080
Explain yourself.

72
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:43,520
Khun Lené went to check the stock
the other day and found the goods we’d hidden.

73
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,120
She refused to let me in.

74
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:49,280
I’m keeping a close eye on her next move.

75
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,080
Then move the stash.

76
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,560
Just as I thought.

77
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,000
Peem and Khun Kanin…

78
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,040
I’m afraid it’ll be difficult now.

79
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,960
She’s watching my every move.

80
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,080
Do whatever it takes.

81
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,880
Make this shipment vanish from Lené’s sight.

82
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:20,200
Wasn't it your job from the start
to keep her in the dark?

83
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:24,280
Handle it. Tonight.

84
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,360
Understood.

85
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,240
I'll get my people on it immediately.

86
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:03,520
That day at the warehouse...

87
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,880
P’ Le.

88
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,280
Didn't I tell you to wait over there?

89
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:15,520
So this means P’ Le might
already know about those two.

90
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:18,480
And she must have seen
something in the warehouse.

91
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:23,360
This might be why she was killed that night.

92
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:52,240
You’re so close to the truth, Rann.

93
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,640
All that's left is to find out
what those goods are.

94
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,640
That warehouse...

95
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:03,640
And that 'special shipment' Khun Kanin mentioned.
That’s where it all began.

96
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,560
I need to get to the bottom of this.

97
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,280
Get it together, Rann.

98
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,480
You’ve got this.

99
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:56,640
You, at the front door.
Report to the assembly point immediately.

100
00:11:57,960 --> 00:12:00,720
Right now? But the shipment
is moving in ten minutes.

101
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,560
I said now!

102
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:11,400
Okay, I’ve got ten minutes.

103
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:40,680
The rear is clear. We’re in position.

104
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:43,880
If they start moving the goods,
we’re ready to breach.

105
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,560
Good. Wait for my signal.

106
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,520
There’s extra stock here.

107
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,120
P’ Le really did know something.

108
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:31,720
These are in the report.

109
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:34,360
But they’re extras.

110
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:37,720
Which means...

111
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,880
Everyone is on standby, Miss.

112
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:21,880
Okay.

113
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:23,680
Now!

114
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,200
Oh, no.

115
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:33,040
Hey! Did you hear that?

116
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,280
It came from the warehouse.
Go check it out.

117
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,240
What’s going on?

118
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:45,520
I don't know.
We haven't made a move yet.

119
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:56,440
Hey! Over there!

120
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,920
- Hey! Stop!
- Stop right now!

121
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:58,880
Rann.

122
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,000
Follow and protect that woman!

123
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,880
- P’ Le.
- You shouldn’t be here.

124
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:41,000
I... I just—

125
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:42,080
Can you run?

126
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,240
- Cover us.
- Yes, Miss.

127
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:53,640
Eyes forward! Don't look back,
and don't stop running!

128
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,560
Did you find them? Who broke in?

129
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:39,840
No sign of them yet, Khun Peem.
All we know is someone’s helping them.

130
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,280
Spread out and surround them, damn it!

131
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,520
Don't let them get away. Go!

132
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:45,320
Yes, sir!

133
00:16:59,160 --> 00:16:59,920
Hey!

134
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,480
- I heard that—
- What happened to her?

135
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:10,400
- Poor her. She was still young.
- A lot of strange things happened that night.

136
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,440
There are rumors going around that Khun Lené got…

137
00:17:14,119 --> 00:17:15,079
P’ Le!

138
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:30,920
I'm the one helping them.

139
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:34,360
You're on your own now, boss.

140
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,200
Hey!

141
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,400
Hey!

142
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:47,240
Stop!

143
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,440
Hey! There they are! After them!

144
00:17:58,960 --> 00:17:59,920
Dammit!

145
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:01,080
What do we do?

146
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:09,800
Huh?

147
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:15,840
Jump!

148
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:16,840
What?!

149
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:53,080
Rann.

150
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:54,440
Rann!

151
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:56,840
Rann!

152
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:00,560
P’ Le!

153
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:05,040
P’ Le! Are you hurt anywhere?
Are you okay?

154
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:07,640
Did you get shot?

155
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:11,440
I’m fine. I’m not hurt.

156
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:15,960
What about you?
Are you hurt anywhere?

157
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:25,520
I was so scared something would happen to you!

158
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:31,160
What would I have done if you’d been shot?

159
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:34,960
I can’t take it.

160
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:36,560
- I can’t take it, P’ Le!
- Rann.

161
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:38,640
- Rann. Rann.
- I’m scared. I’m so scared, P’ Le!

162
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:40,680
I would have felt so guilty.

163
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:41,880
Rann.

164
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,520
I’m fine.

165
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,080
It’s okay. I’m right here.

166
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:25,480
We can't go home tonight.
It's too dangerous.

167
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:32,840
Let’s just stay here.

168
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:34,440
But this place is—

169
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:36,360
Just go.

170
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:12,040
Khun Lené... about... about today...

171
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,640
Go take a shower first.

172
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:14,680
But—

173
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:17,320
Just go! Look at yourself.

174
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,720
You’re a total mess.

175
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:53,880
- Still in one piece, boss?
- I’m safe. Don't worry.

176
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:10,280
Sir, someone broke into the warehouse tonight.

177
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:17,080
Was it Lené?

178
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,280
No, Sir.

179
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,600
All we know is that it was a woman.

180
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,960
But based on her build, it wasn’t Khun Lené.

181
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:27,360
We almost had her, but
someone helped her get away.

182
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,920
And what did she take?

183
00:22:32,840 --> 00:22:36,280
The shipping documents are missing.
And our crates were pried open.

184
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:40,600
I’ve ordered the goods moved
and pushed back the pickup date.

185
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:43,560
Until we're sure it’s safe.

186
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,600
Find out who she is.

187
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:53,040
And find out who helped her.

188
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:02,040
Go back and check...
See if my daughter is home yet.

189
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:03,400
Yes, sir.

190
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:29,120
Rann.

191
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:35,840
We need to talk.

192
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:37,920
Yes.

193
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:40,240
I want to talk too.

194
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:49,080
Do you have any idea how
dangerous what you did today was?

195
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,400
I know.

196
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:53,320
You could have died.

197
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:55,880
I knew that too.

198
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:59,400
Then why did you do it if you knew?

199
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:01,440
Because I couldn't just let it go.

200
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,360
And why is that?

201
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:07,320
Do you realize if I’d been even a second later...

202
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:10,760
you could have died?

203
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,360
But I’m not dead, am I?

204
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,280
Aran!

205
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:18,400
What about you?
What exactly are you risking your life for?

206
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:28,720
I know what I did was stupid.

207
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:33,200
No matter how you look at it, I'm just
a stupid girl who rushed in there alone.

208
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,320
And I got absolutely nothing.

209
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:41,440
Even the phone with the evidence
is at the bottom of the river now.

210
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:48,360
But I only had to do this because
you never tell me anything!

211
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:52,800
Oh, so it's my fault then?

212
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:54,720
No, it isn’t.

213
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:58,160
I know you don’t trust me.

214
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:02,080
And I’m not asking you
to start trusting me overnight.

215
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,760
I just wanted to find the truth myself.

216
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:11,120
Because I heard your father talking
to Peem about moving some goods today.

217
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:16,080
So you were stupid enough to run in there
alone just to find some goddamn truth?!

218
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:21,720
I did all of this for you.

219
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,440
Because I'm worried about you.

220
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:31,640
Everyone around you has bad intentions.

221
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:34,920
You can be mad at me,
or hate me all you want.

222
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,280
But I’m begging you...

223
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:42,160
- Don't trust those people.
- Peem is the one I trust the most.

224
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:50,120
You don’t understand.

225
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,560
I understand everything!

226
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,720
You're the one who doesn't get it!

227
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,360
Peem was never one of my father’s men.

228
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:21,440
Khun Kanin wants me to move the goods tonight.

229
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:24,320
Good.

230
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:27,960
Then we’ll raid the warehouse
tonight as originally planned.

231
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:30,520
Get the team ready.

232
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:31,880
Understood.

233
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:34,920
I’ll cause a distraction
on Khun Kanin’s side first.

234
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,520
Once I give the signal, make your move.

235
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:42,920
It’s just that...

236
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:47,120
he might be a little suspicious of me.

237
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,440
Maybe it’s time for you to come back.

238
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:57,160
We must destroy this shipment no matter what.

239
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,240
We need to cut off my father’s cash flow.

240
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:04,320
Besides... those things could
even lead to more deaths.

241
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:12,600
Khun Lené.

242
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:16,880
Please be careful.

243
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:22,200
You dare to warn someone like me?

244
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,560
I know my boss is capable.

245
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:31,760
But your people are only
human, in case you forgot.

246
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:40,440
I was the one who sent Peem
to work for my father.

247
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:45,240
He is my man.

248
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:49,560
You get it now, right?

249
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:52,280
If you do…

250
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,720
- don't ever do it again.
- What about me?

251
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:57,240
What?

252
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,440
If Khun Peem is your man...

253
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:04,360
then what am I?

254
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:05,920
Exactly.

255
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:09,440
Where do you fit into this equation?

256
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:13,880
You really don't know, P’ Le?

257
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,040
All of this…

258
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:18,440
that I’ve done...

259
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:20,400
I don’t.

260
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:23,040
And I don’t want to know either.

261
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,760
You’re the one who needs to stop.

262
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:29,520
Stop risking your life! Stop everything!

263
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:33,560
Pack your things and
go back to your peaceful life.

264
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:36,120
Stop meddling in my business.

265
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,000
All you ever do is push me away.

266
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:43,480
Do you think I can’t feel pain?

267
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:45,200
If staying with me is so painful…

268
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:49,280
then go.

269
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:52,680
You know I can’t do that!

270
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:03,120
I have no one else left in my life.

271
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,000
You know that.

272
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:13,920
You’ve known all along since
that day how I feel about you.

273
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:20,160
You know that you’re my entire world!

274
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:24,480
If your whole world was about to collapse,

275
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:29,080
would you just stand there
and watch it disappear?!

276
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,160
I can’t do it!

277
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:37,680
I can't bear the thought of it!

278
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:44,520
I’m not asking for much.

279
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:49,240
You don’t have to love me.

280
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,720
You don’t have trust me.

281
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:56,040
You can just think of me as an ordinary employee.

282
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:01,320
But I’m only asking for one thing.

283
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,000
Please don’t chase me away.

284
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:13,440
Why?

285
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:18,200
Why do you have to go this far?

286
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:21,640
Because we only have one life.

287
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:24,680
And I don't want to lose you again!

288
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,480
Can you stop pushing me away?

289
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,360
Please, no more.

290
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:49,880
Don’t chase me away.

291
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:53,240
Rann.

292
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:08,520
I love you, P’ Le.

293
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:59,400
This time... can you not push me away again?

294
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:33,720
You said it yourself.

295
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:36,480
Yes.

296
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:38,880
I did.

297
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:51,840
You're so much cuter when
you’re not being fierce with me.

298
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:52,040
What’s on your mind, sir?

299
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:59,960
Do you think this girl is my daughter’s type?

300
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:02,120
What do you mean by that, sir?

301
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:10,480
How could I not know that my daughter
has never once dated a man?

302
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:16,800
Perhaps she has a very specific taste.

303
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:22,080
Especially for girls like her.

304
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,040
So that's why you chose to hire her?

305
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:31,640
If someone doesn't have a weakness,

306
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,840
you just have to create one for them.

307
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,360
Where did you get those clothes from?

308
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:55,200
Get changed.

309
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,120
It’s safe now.

310
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:59,280
Peem is picking us up at a restaurant nearby.

311
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,240
Thank you, P’ Le.

312
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:12,440
From now on, can I go back to calling you P' Le?

313
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,280
Call me whatever you want.

314
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,240
Thank you.

315
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:27,960
Rann!

316
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:06,560
Why are you staring at my hand?

317
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:08,640
Pervert.

318
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:10,200
I am not!

319
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:28,840
So, what did you find out last night?

320
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:39,520
I found something hidden in
the company's shipping list.

321
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:42,840
And I found some documents too.

322
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,920
I didn't have time to look through them,

323
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:50,120
but I think the documents were falsified.

324
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:54,720
So I think the truth behind this company

325
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:57,240
is that they're smuggling illegal weapons.

326
00:38:58,440 --> 00:38:59,360
Am I right?

327
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:05,760
You’ve been working there for weeks.

328
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:08,560
Did you only just realize what this company does?

329
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:13,960
It’s not just illegal weapons.

330
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:27,840
So... your father...

331
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:33,800
Exactly.

332
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,240
That’s why I didn't want
you to get involved in this.

333
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,240
It's too late for that.

334
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:44,200
Are you only starting to regret it now?

335
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:48,920
No.

336
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:52,880
Not for a second have I ever
regretted coming back to you.

337
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:01,600
Even if I had to choose a thousand lives over…

338
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,200
I’d still come back to you.

339
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:08,400
Always.

340
00:40:19,200 --> 00:40:20,360
I give up.

341
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:35,960
Some secretary you are.

342
00:40:37,040 --> 00:40:40,440
Don't you know how expensive it
is to hire protection for someone?

343
00:40:43,640 --> 00:40:45,520
Why should I spend money to protect you anyway?

344
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,800
I can take care of myself.

345
00:40:51,040 --> 00:40:54,200
A funeral is more expensive than a bodyguard.

346
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:01,440
Would it kill you to just say
you're worried about me?

347
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,160
Wait here.

348
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:16,440
Hm?

349
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:37,600
P’ Le.

350
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:39,640
What are you doing?

351
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,240
- P’ Le.
- Just sit still.

352
00:41:45,360 --> 00:41:47,240
No, what are you doing?

353
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:49,120
Why are you on the floor?

354
00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:53,600
Can't you just sit still and
act helpless like you used to?

355
00:42:08,480 --> 00:42:10,280
If you can't open it, just tell me.

356
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:11,400
P’ Le.

357
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:14,440
Are you going to open it for me?

358
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:20,160
Here.

359
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:24,280
You really can't do anything yourself, can you?

360
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:29,880
Looks like you'll just have
to have me around forever.

361
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:50,880
~ I can only look back on days
that have turned to dust ~

362
00:42:52,160 --> 00:43:00,240
~ A Time when I let you walk away ~
P’ Le still remembers.
She remembers everything... about us.

363
00:43:01,520 --> 00:43:04,120
I’ve missed this smile so much.

364
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:12,960
Done.

365
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:16,920
Your old pair was ruined
when you jumped into the water.

366
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:17,800
Just throw them away.

367
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:27,960
And this is to replace the one that’s underwater.

368
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:35,720
Wait, P’ Le.

369
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:43,360
Well… about last night…

370
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:47,400
Last night?

371
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:51,320
Well... when we...

372
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:53,800
You and me...

373
00:43:55,320 --> 00:43:59,400
I mean… our relationship now.

374
00:44:04,360 --> 00:44:05,760
You’re my secretary.

375
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:09,040
And I’m your boss.

376
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:13,360
Is that all?

377
00:44:18,920 --> 00:44:22,240
Can’t accept it?
You can always go back abroad.

378
00:44:22,680 --> 00:44:23,520
No way.

379
00:44:25,360 --> 00:44:26,840
I'm fine with having no status.

380
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:32,840
But let me stay here, by your side.
Because—

381
00:44:34,600 --> 00:44:35,960
I’m already yours.

382
00:44:37,440 --> 00:44:39,720
I mean, I’m your person now, P’Le.

383
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:48,680
Mhm. Have it your way then.

384
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:53,160
Can we go now?

385
00:44:54,560 --> 00:44:55,360
Yes.

386
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:39,120
Your boss is so mean to me, P’ Dia.

387
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:42,520
Hmm? I think she’s actually kind.

388
00:45:43,240 --> 00:45:44,320
How exactly?

389
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:46,920
You know the answer to that already, Khun Rann.

390
00:45:49,400 --> 00:45:51,240
You mean the shoes and the heel grips, right?

391
00:45:52,160 --> 00:45:53,840
And there’s the car too.

392
00:45:54,040 --> 00:45:57,600
Before you came along, Khun Lené
loved sports cars more than anything.

393
00:45:58,400 --> 00:46:00,160
Mhm, I know.

394
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:03,560
I know she’s kind.
I’ve known that all along.

395
00:46:05,080 --> 00:46:07,440
She might be mean sometimes,

396
00:46:08,280 --> 00:46:09,920
but she’s still the kindest person.

397
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:14,120
Even though she’s being so brutal right now...

398
00:46:16,040 --> 00:46:18,480
I don't want to give up, P’ Dia.

399
00:46:19,360 --> 00:46:22,920
I’ve given up before.
I’ve walked away once already.

400
00:46:23,360 --> 00:46:25,520
And I know how much it hurts.

401
00:46:27,880 --> 00:46:32,320
At least I’m old enough now to know
it wasn't all in my head that day.

402
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:35,520
P’ Le must have had her reasons.

403
00:46:43,960 --> 00:46:48,120
I want to see just how
mean she can really be to me.

404
00:46:54,080 --> 00:46:55,080
Is that so?

405
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:02,840
I already made a certain someone cry all night.

406
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:07,240
Want to put that to the test again?

407
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:30,680
Get me a cup of coffee.

408
00:47:32,440 --> 00:47:35,840
It seems I didn't get enough sleep last night.

409
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:48,560
Have some breakfast first, P’ Le.
We've got some time today.

410
00:47:48,600 --> 00:47:50,360
Aren't you going to ask me 'time for what'?

411
00:47:50,520 --> 00:47:51,640
So what is this time for?

412
00:47:51,920 --> 00:47:53,400
Time to win your heart.

413
00:47:54,680 --> 00:47:56,400
Aran, get me some coffee.

414
00:47:58,280 --> 00:48:00,200
I thought you’d have me instead.

415
00:48:01,160 --> 00:48:04,600
For the past few days… you’ve
been making a move on me, right?

416
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:09,120
If I told you what I was going to do,
you’d just try to stop me again.

417
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:11,400
But I'm interested in you.

418
00:48:14,320 --> 00:48:15,080
P' Le!

419
00:48:16,440 --> 00:48:17,560
Don't cross the line.

420
00:48:18,400 --> 00:48:21,400
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.
